// Assuming you have icons for different weather conditions
const weatherIconMap = {
    '01d': require('./Assets/clear.png'), // clear sky day
    '01n': require('./assets/icons/nt_clear.png'), // clear sky night
    '02d': require('./assets/icons/few_clouds.png'), // few clouds day
    '02n': require('./assets/icons/nt_few_clouds.png'), // few clouds night
    '03d': require('./assets/icons/scattered_clouds.png'), // scattered clouds day
    '03n': require('./assets/icons/nt_scattered_clouds.png'), // scattered clouds night
    '04d': require('./assets/icons/broken_clouds.png'), // broken clouds day
    '04n': require('./assets/icons/nt_broken_clouds.png'), // broken clouds night
    '09d': require('./assets/icons/shower_rain.png'), // shower rain day
    '09n': require('./assets/icons/nt_shower_rain.png'), // shower rain night
    '10d': require('./assets/icons/rain.png'), // rain day
    '10n': require('./assets/icons/nt_rain.png'), // rain night
    '11d': require('./assets/icons/thunderstorm.png'), // thunderstorm day
    '11n': require('./assets/icons/nt_thunderstorm.png'), // thunderstorm night
    '13d': require('./assets/icons/snow.png'), // snow day
    '13n': require('./assets/icons/nt_snow.png'), // snow night
    '50d': require('./assets/icons/mist.png'), // mist day
    '50n': require('./assets/icons/nt_mist.png'), // mist night
    'default': require('./assets/icons/default.png'), // default icon
  };
  
  export default weatherIconMap;
